"n.哨兵，卫兵 【英】 n.哨兵,卫兵(sentry; lookout) 【考】 sentinel : watchful / epicure : discriminating(卫兵的特点是警戒/ 美食家的特点是有识 别力的) n. 哨兵, 卫兵 【记】sent感觉, inel: 要提高感觉的人－哨兵 【参】sentry(n 哨兵) 【类】sentinel: watchful = epicure: discriminating卫兵的特点是警戒的 = 美食家的特点是有识别力的 【记】sent + tunnel 感觉隧道的动静的是哨兵 sentinel (n.)  1570s, from Middle French sentinelle (16c.), from Italian sentinella ""a sentinel."" OED says ""No convincing etymology of the It. word has been proposed,"" but perhaps (via a notion of ""perceive, watch""), from sentire ""to hear,"" from Latin sentire ""feel, perceive by the senses"" (see sense (n.))."
